Name the browser tab after the RDP host.

Stock gateway-ui leaves the tab title hardcoded to "Devolutions Gateway"
(index.html) and never calls setTitle, so every open session tab is
indistinguishable. We set document.title to the connection hostname once the
web-session form data is loaded. This touches text only; the favicon
(<link rel="icon">) is untouched, so the logo stays.

Set directly on document.title rather than via Angular's Title service to keep
this a one-line additive patch (no constructor/DI change). No TitleStrategy is
configured upstream, so nothing resets the title on navigation.

--- a/webapp/apps/gateway-ui/src/client/app/modules/web-client/rdp/web-client-rdp.component.ts
+++ b/webapp/apps/gateway-ui/src/client/app/modules/web-client/rdp/web-client-rdp.component.ts
@@ -153,6 +153,8 @@ export class WebClientRdpComponent extends DesktopWebClientBaseComponent impleme
   private getFormData(): Observable<void> {
     return from(this.webSessionService.getWebSession(this.webSessionId)).pipe(
       map((currentWebSession) => {
         this.formData = currentWebSession.data as RdpFormDataInput;
+        // devget: name the browser tab after the RDP host (favicon untouched).
+        document.title = this.formData.hostname;
         this.sessionInfoUsername = this.formData.username;
         this.refreshSessionInfo();
       }),
